{
  "doc_id": "49768",
  "text": "Therefore, we have chosen a categorically different strategy to visualize molecular biomarkers for DR. The current requirement for a biomarker is objective measurement as an indicator of pathogenic processes. [CITATION_1] For effective and timely prevention of retinopathy, a biomarker should be non-invasively detectable in the early subclinical disease stage, such as in the period before capillaries obliterate. Furthermore, the ideal biomarker should be causally linked to retinal pathology development. [CITATION_2] In diabetes, the microvascular endothelium is known to express ICAM-1. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] Endothelial ICAM-1 binds to leukocyte β2 integrins and results in leukocyte accumulation in retinal microvessels. Binding of the β2 integrins to the endothelial ICAM-1 in experimental DR subsequently leads to opening of the blood retinal barrier and leakage. [CITATION_5] Our current approach is to target retinal endothelial ICAM-1 as an indicator of early pathology.",
